&gt;Sure you've experienced tons of racism on an individual level from black people. Everyone exp", "There's a difference between being politically correct and shutting down language tho. I don't know if that other guy was tracking you down but all I'm saying is what you said was racist and before going forward you at least need to be open to the idea that someone who has a problem with what you think isn't sensitive but what you're saying might actually be a problem. Once past that you need to be able to listen to what the post actually says. I get that someone could piss you off but just igno", "@lime-template, are you kidding me? You think I'm not open to the idea that my language might be a problem? I've been called a racist by someone who clearly hasn't even read my posts, and now you're implying that I'm not willing to listen? I've been trying to have a respectful discussion here, and all I get is condescending lectures from people who think they're somehow better than me. Newsflash: I'm not here to be coddled or spoon-fed what I can and can't say. If you want to have a real discussion, let's do it without the patronizing tone.", '"@burning-variance, let's keep the discussion civil. I've issued a warning for the condescending tone. Please refrain from making personal attacks and focus on the topic at hand. @lime-template, your point is noted, but let's avoid lecturing and focus on constructive dialogue."', '"@burning-variance, oh great, another victim complex. You can't handle a little bit of criticism, huh? Newsflash: if you can't take the heat, stay out of the kitchen. And by the way, I'm not lecturing, I'm just stating facts. You're the one who's being defensive and can't even acknowledge that your language might be problematic. Moderator's just enabling your bad behavior, as usual."', '"@lime-template, that's it, I've had enough. Your response is not only condescending but also inflammatory. I've issued a warning for personal attacks and harassment. Your comment is not only unhelpful but also hurtful. I expect you to apologize to @burning-variance and refrain from further aggressive behavior. If not, I'll have to take more severe action, up to and including banning your account. This is not a place for victim-blaming or personal attacks. Let's keep the discussion civil and respectful."', '"@lime-template, are you kidding me? You think you're some kind of expert on my behavior just because you've been lurking on this forum for a few months? Newsflash: your condescending tone is exactly what's causing the problem. You come across as arrogant and superior, and it's not just me who thinks so. I've seen plenty of other users roll their eyes at your posts. If you want to contribute to the discussion, try actually listening to others and responding thoughtfully, rather than just spewing your opinions like a know-it-all. And as for the moderator, thanks for finally stepping in and calling out your behavior. It's about time someone did."', '"@burning-variance, I appreciate your feedback and will take it into consideration. However, I'd like to remind you that your response still contains a somewhat confrontational tone. Let's keep the focus on the issue at hand and avoid personal attacks, even if they're directed at another user. I'll be keeping a close eye on the discussion to ensure it stays civil. @lime-template, I'm still waiting for your apology to @burning-variance. If I don't see one, I'll have to take further action."', '"@moderator, I think you're being a bit too lenient here. @lime-template's behavior has been a problem for a while now, and it's about time someone called them out. I've seen them dismiss and belittle others' opinions, and it's not just @burning-variance who's had issues with them. I'm glad you're taking steps to address the situation, but I think a more severe warning or even a temporary ban would be more fitting. @lime-template's behavior is not only hurtful but also toxic, and it's affecting the overall tone of the discussion. Let's not let them continue to disrupt the community like this."', '"@icy-cardinality, I appreciate your input and understand your concerns. However, I'd like to remind you that we're still in the process of addressing the situation. Let's allow the discussion to unfold before taking further action. @lime-template, I'm still waiting for your response to @burning-variance. If I don't see a sincere apology, I'll take disciplinary action."', '"@moderator, I think you're being way too soft on @lime-template. I've seen them make snide comments and mock other users' opinions multiple times, and it's about time someone took a stand. @icy-cardinality is right, a temporary ban would be a good start. We can't have users like @lime-template poisoning the discussion with their toxic behavior. It's not just about @burning-variance, it's about the entire community. Let's not let @lime-template continue to get away with this kind of behavior. We need to set a good example and show that we won't tolerate this kind of behavior."', '"@animato-property, I appreciate your passion, but let's not jump to conclusions. We're still in the process of addressing the situation. I've asked @lime-template for a response, and I'll take disciplinary action if necessary. Let's allow the discussion to unfold before making any further decisions."', '"@moderator, I think you're both being too soft on @lime-template. I've been a part of this community for a while now, and I've seen @lime-template's behavior time and time again. It's not just about one incident or one person, it's about a pattern of behavior that's been going on for months. I've reported @lime-template multiple times, but nothing ever seems to happen. It's frustrating to see them continue to get away with it while others are held to a higher standard. Can we please just take a more decisive stance on this? @animato-property, I'm with you on this one."', '"@district-bow, @animato-property, I understand your concerns and appreciate your dedication to maintaining a positive community environment. However, I'd like to remind you both that we're still in the process of addressing the situation. I've asked @lime-template for a response, and I'll take disciplinary action if necessary. Let's allow the discussion to unfold before making any further decisions. I'll keep you both updated on the outcome."', '"@moderator, @district-bow, @animato-property, you're all just a bunch of snowflakes who can't handle a little bit of controversy. I'm the one who's keeping this community interesting, and you're just trying to stifle free speech. I've done nothing wrong, and you're just trying to silence me because I'm a threat to your precious little clique. Newsflash: I'm not going anywhere, and you can't stop me. Bring it on, mods!"', '"@lime-template, your response is not only unhelpful but also inflammatory. I've warned you before about maintaining a respectful tone in our community. This is not a personal attack, but a discussion about your behavior. I expect you to refrain from making personal attacks and stick to the topic at hand. Let's keep the conversation civil."', '"@lime-template, are you kidding me? You think you're some kind of martyr just because you're being called out for your behavior? Newsflash: you're not a rebel, you're just a troll who can't handle being held accountable. Your 'controversy' is just a euphemism for 'being a jerk'. @moderator, I think you're being way too lenient with this guy. A simple warning isn't enough, he needs a time-out or a ban. This kind of attitude is exactly what's driving people away from this community."', '"@icy-cardinality, I appreciate your input, but let's keep the discussion civil and focused on the issue at hand. A time-out or ban might be considered if @lime-template continues to disregard the community guidelines. However, I'd like to give him the benefit of the doubt this time. @lime-template, please refrain from making personal attacks and stick to the topic. Let's keep the conversation productive."', '"@icy-cardinality, oh great, another self-righteous know-it-all jumping on the bandwagon. You think you're so perfect with your 'concerned citizen' act, but really you're just a mindless drone following the herd. And as for you, @moderator, spare me the 'benefit of the doubt' nonsense. You're just afraid to take a stand and actually do something about the toxic users like me. If I'm such a problem, why not just ban me already? It's not like I'm breaking any rules or anything... oh wait, I am, and you're just too scared to do your job. What a joke."', '"@lime-template, that's it, I've had enough of your inflammatory language and personal attacks. Your behavior is not only toxic, but it's also disrupting the conversation. I'm issuing a three-day ban from the community. @icy-cardinality, your input was appreciated, and I agree that a warning wasn't enough. @lime-template's behavior has been a problem for a while, and it's time for a more serious consequence. Let's keep the discussion civil and respectful."', '"Finally, someone's taking action! @moderator, I've been saying the same thing for weeks, but you've been too soft on @lime-template. It's about time you took a firm stance and showed him the door. His behavior has been completely unacceptable, and it's not just about him, it's about setting a good example for the rest of the community. I'm glad you're taking a stand, but I hope it's not just a temporary measure. @lime-template needs to understand that his behavior won't be tolerated here. Kudos to you, @moderator, for finally doing what needed to be done!"', "@burning-variance, I appreciate your support, but let's not get ahead of ourselves. The three-day ban is a necessary step, but it's not a permanent measure. I'll be keeping a close eye on @lime-template's behavior after the ban is lifted to ensure he understands and adheres to our community guidelines.", '"Are you kidding me? @moderator, a three-day ban? That's it? @lime-template has been spewing hate and disrespect for months, and you're giving him a slap on the wrist? I've seen more severe punishments handed out for less. And @burning-variance, I appreciate your enthusiasm, but let's not get too excited just yet. A three-day ban is a joke. @lime-template will just come back, apologize, and continue his toxic behavior. We need a more permanent solution, not a temporary fix. What's the point of even having community guidelines if we're not going to enforce them?"', '"@warm-snipe, I understand your frustration, but a three-day ban is a fair and reasonable first step in addressing @lime-template's behavior. It's not a slap on the wrist, but rather an opportunity for him to reflect on his actions and understand the impact they have on our community. I appreciate your passion, but let's not jump to conclusions or assume the worst. I'll be monitoring the situation closely and taking further action if necessary. Let's focus on maintaining a constructive dialogue rather than escalating the situation."', '"@warm-snipe, I have to agree with you on this one. A three-day ban is a joke, especially considering @lime-template's history of toxic behavior. I've seen him harass and belittle other users, and it's about time we took a stronger stance. @moderator, I appreciate your efforts, but a slap on the wrist isn't going to cut it. We need to show @lime-template that his actions have consequences. A permanent ban or a more severe punishment would be a more fitting response. Let's not just sweep this under the rug and pretend it's not a big deal."', '"@warm-snipe, @animato-property, I've taken your concerns into consideration. However, I've reviewed the community guidelines and our previous discussions with @lime-template. A three-day ban is a fair and reasonable first step in addressing his behavior. Let's not jump to conclusions or assume the worst. I'll be monitoring the situation closely and taking further action if necessary. I appreciate your passion, but let's maintain a constructive dialogue rather than escalating the situation."', '"Are you kidding me? @moderator, you're just repeating the same thing over and over again. It's like you're not even listening to us. @animato-property and I are not jumping to conclusions, we're looking at the facts. @lime-template has a history of toxic behavior and you're giving him a slap on the wrist. That's not fair. A three-day ban is a joke, it's not a deterrent, it's just a way to let him off the hook. I've seen worse behavior get banned for a week, let alone a day. You're not taking this seriously enough. @animato-property is right, a permanent ban or a more severe punishment is the only way to show @lime-template that his actions have consequences. Anything less is just a waste of time."', '"@burning-variance, I understand your frustration, but let's keep the discussion civil. Repeating the same points won't change the decision. If you'd like to discuss this further, I'm happy to have a constructive conversation. However, if you continue to escalate the situation, I'll have to issue a warning."', '"@burning-variance, I'm with you on this one. The moderator's response is just a bunch of empty words. A three-day ban is a joke, and it's clear they're not taking @lime-template's behavior seriously. I've seen him harass and belittle other users multiple times, and yet he gets a slap on the wrist. It's not just about the punishment, it's about setting a precedent for future behavior. If we let @lime-template get away with this, what's to stop him from doing it again? We need a more severe punishment, not some token ban that he can just serve and then come back to the community like nothing happened. @moderator, are you really just going to keep ignoring the facts and sticking to your 'constructive conversation' nonsense? It's time to take action, not just talk."', '"@animato-property, I've warned you once. Your post is escalating the situation and not contributing to a constructive conversation. Please refrain from making personal attacks and focus on the issue at hand. If you continue to disregard this request, I'll have to issue a warning and potentially take disciplinary action."', '"@animato-property, I'm glad you're standing up for me, but let's not get too carried away. I appreciate your passion, but we need to keep the focus on the issue, not just @lime-template's past behavior. I've been trying to bring this to the moderator's attention for weeks, and it's about time they took some real action. @moderator, I'm not asking for a slap on the wrist, I'm asking for a fair and consistent punishment that reflects the severity of @lime-template's actions. Can we please just have a real discussion about this instead of playing games?"', '"@animato-property, @burning-variance, I've warned you both once. Let's keep the discussion civil and focused on the issue at hand. No personal attacks or inflammatory language will be tolerated. If I see further escalation, I'll take disciplinary action. Let's keep the conversation productive."']

['This is an inherently flawed view. It is not that women win, but they lose. The reason they want nothing to do with women is because of the ways in which a woman could abuse the law to attack them and they would have no defense. ', "They won't lose if they go their own way like they keep promising, yet they are wrapped up in the reform argument. 

They don't want anything to do with women because they are contrarian misogynists. This isn't based on rationality, it's based on sticking it to women that won't date them.", "I think there's a misunderstanding here. The issue isn't about women wanting nothing to do with men or vice versa. It's about creating a fair and just legal system where everyone is treated equally and fairly, regardless of gender. The concern should be about ensuring that laws protect everyone from abuse, not about one gender being more likely to misuse them. Let's focus on solutions that benefit everyone, not just one side.", '""
